==English==

===Pronunciation===
*fŏ'rəd, /ˈfɒrəd/, /"fQr@d/
*fô(r)'hĕd, /ˈfɔː(r)hed/, /"fO:(r)hed/

Despite the fact that the word ''forehead'' looks as if it were composed by ''fore'' and ''head'', its traditional [[Wikipedia:List_of_words_of_disputed_pronunciation#F|pronunciation]] is {{IPA|/ˈfɒɹɪd/}} (FORrid, rhymes with ''horrid''), even if the more logical pronunciation {{IPA|/ˈfɔː(ɹ)hɛd/}} is becoming more common.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{anatomy}} The part of the [[face]] above the [[eyebrow]]s and below the hairline.

